Date Reviewed: 27/03/08 CeeKay69 Member Since: 27/03/08
View Member's: Reviews Scan are the best PC company I have had the pleasure to deal with. I purchased 3XS V3 Gamer system from them which is just fantastic. This is my first PC I have bought for gaming & I am not disappointed with the quality, or performance. I couldn't find a better price anywhere & the customer service provided was friendly & never SALESMAN. They wanted to help & build the right machine. These guys have really pride in their products & rightly so. Well Done SCAN...... :) Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 02/01/08 OccupyingSpirit Member Since: 02/01/08
View Member's: Reviews I have to agree with the other reviewers. I bought a 3XS 680i computer, it arrived within two weeks (just before Xmas), and is a top product. Apart from being beautifully made, it runs even quieter than my old Dell, and I believe the price to be competitive. The sales advice was expert, and not directed toward getting me to spend more. If anything, the reverse. Well done guys, I recommend these people. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 06/12/07 coling Member Since: 06/12/07
View Member's: Reviews I ordered a new PC from Scan and have been very impressed with the quality of service that I have received at every stage. The customisation options on the site are excellent with lots of detail about each component. Feedback on the build progress is head and shoulders above anything else I have seen - you even see a mugshot of the person that completed each build stage! The system itself arrived on the date that I specified, was very well packaged and has come exactly as specified (no trialware!). I can't recommend this company highly enough and have already placed another order with them. Excellent! Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 09/11/07 guysym Member Since: 09/11/07
View Member's: Reviews The 6 days it took was for building the computer and delivery which is far quicker than i expected it to be. The system is fantastic and exactly what I required. The 3XS team kept me up to date with the construction of my system with regular emails and updates on their website so I could view my system throughout its build. Excellent company, I will definatly buy from them again. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 21/06/07 DavidAYoung Member Since: 21/06/07
View Member's: Reviews Without hesitation I would buy from this merchant. One of the best experiences ever which I would strongly recommend to anyone. Staff were courteous, helpful and extremely knowledgeable. The best of components were used and the ensuing build simply first class - a thing of great beauty! Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 04/06/07 davedontmind Member Since: 04/06/07
View Member's: Reviews Easy to use web interface to configre the machine I required. The initial motherboard was out of stock, but Scan suggested a suitable replacement which I'm very happy with. Good delivery time, quality kit, and it runs great. I've bought a system from Scan before, and I wouldn't hesitate to buy from them again. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 23/05/07 DarkPsychosis Member Since: 23/05/07
View Member's: Reviews The pc selection and customisation worked perfectly, I could select every component I wanted without getting anything I didn't want. The order tracking shows where in their 10 stage system the order is and even who's working on it right now with a little photo and a technicians profile (It's nice to put a face to a name). On the occasions I talked to customer service, they always knew their stuff and were genuinly nice to talk to. Everything arrived on the requested day and eveything worked perfectly without trouble. The best customer experience I've had with any company for years, can't say better. I'd give them six out of five stars if I could. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 18/05/07 valleykarate Member Since: 18/05/07
View Member's: Reviews I bought nearly Â£500 worth of components and it was worth every penny just for the customer service and customer support alone. Every single person I spoke to was polite, helpfull and all knew their stuff. Well done Scan good service is so hard to find these days. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 17/04/07 swift001 Member Since: 17/04/07
View Member's: Reviews I bought a custom-build PC from Scan/3xs, and the overall service was first class. Components were selected from a well-chosen range, and when a component supply issue arose, the guys knew their stuff, and suggested good alternatives. The unit was fully tested before despatch, and very well packed. Build quality was excellent, and I am very pleased with the result. I would certainly buy from them again. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 01/04/07 Darrenvsl Member Since: 01/04/07
View Member's: Reviews Scan 3XS systems, are the only systems that I rely on as a professional, just upgraded to the intel quad! its quick, very quick! the build quality, design and customer service from scan means I can't be bothered to go elsewhere. Keep it up guys. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 26/03/07 rain426 Member Since: 26/03/07
View Member's: Reviews There is simply no reason to buy anything from any other supplier. Scan are superb! I had an item in my order that was out of stock, so I called their customer service department to amend it. My call was answered immediately by a very friendly, helpful person who promptly amended my order as I requested. An hour later, I had an email from Scan telling me my order had been despatched and I should expect delivery the following day. Bear in mind I had only paid for a standard delivery, not next day delivery. I now recommend Scan to all my friends and colleagues, and to anyone reading this review! Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 21/03/07 RiFaWa Member Since: 21/03/07
View Member's: Reviews Excellent customer service. When I emailed with a pre-order query I received a helpful email reply within about 30 minutes. After I placed my order one of the items I had chosen was out of stock, but again, a customer service agent was able to make alternative suggestions again within about 30 minutes. I was kept up-to-date by email through all steges of the delivery process and my order arrived promptly and well packed. I will certainly be very happy to buy from Scan Computers again. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 19/03/07 WaYn3 Member Since: 19/03/07
View Member's: Reviews Seriously if you are thinking about ordering from somewhere else, don't... It's just soo much quicker and easier to do it through Scan, the level of service that they present each customer with is not only outstanding its mind boggling! You are made to feel like their only customer with the utmost attention and care. The packaging of the products is bordering on rediculously good, and if anything ever goes wrong the Scan RMA service is simply the best! Quite simply amazing experience! Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 14/03/07 rayygun Member Since: 14/03/07
View Member's: Reviews What a fantastic service. This was my first purchase with Scan. I decided to put all my eggs in one basket and buy most of the parts for my new build from yourselves. Delivery was on the right day, all packaged perfectly. No items missing, all items in working order, plus great prices. Highly recomended. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 05/03/07 Hybridize Member Since: 05/03/07
View Member's: Reviews All aspects of the shopping experience were very simplistic and pleasurable to use. Customer service is excellent as well as their on time delivery, sometimes i even recieve my orders before the due date which is as added bonus. If anyone is debating about whether to order from this company you have my recommendation, an excellent company to deal with. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 21/02/07 GazzerJ Member Since: 21/02/07
View Member's: Reviews Excellent service from Scan. Placed a large order for components for a new Home PC. Items delivered promptly, very well packaged indeed and all present and correct, no mistakes. Built the PC as a surprise Christmas present for my boy, booted first time, no problems, thanks to SCAN for an excellent job makes a nice change from the usual hassle of internet trading Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 15/02/07 Bruce519 Member Since: 15/02/07
View Member's: Reviews I purchased a DVR-111D DVD/CDwriter, email & text messages imformed me of progress from clearing payment to delivery.It arrived very well packed & in good condition I felt confident from their easy to use web site that this would go well, and it did. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 09/02/07 Nightwatch Member Since: 09/02/07
View Member's: Reviews I am a software author & systems builder. Recently I bought an ASUS EN7950GT PCI-E graphics card,a Pentium D 3.4 CPU, Corsair 2Gb 667MHz DDR2 RAM, an Arctic FreezerPro heatsink/fan. Shopping on the site was very easy and informative. I am very careful in decision making process and I found that, rather gladly, Scan Computers' knowledge base and support is second to none. Later, I was kept informed at every stage of the delivery, which was absolutely flawless. Prices? They were the best, too. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 26/01/07 thesnappleking Member Since: 26/01/07
View Member's: Reviews Good quality work done, would recommend to anyone. I got a 3XS, system arrived the day after completion. Got a loose cable during shipping, but the technican knew which cable was loose (i kept thinking 4pin). Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 22/01/07 ScottTH Member Since: 22/01/07
View Member's: Reviews Shipping would have taken 3 working days but I chose to use the QCollect service. I was most impressed with the low prices, easy web site navigation and speed in processing my order. The time from order being placed by myself to it being ready to collect was 45 minutes. I was then able to collect the order the following morning. On arrival I had the product in my hand within a couple of minutes. Well Organised all round service. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 19/01/07 Matroxx Member Since: 19/01/07
View Member's: Reviews SCAN have supplied us with an entire network infrastructure, personal computers and a high spec laptop. All of this was delivered expediantly and handled very well through highly capable customer service agents. We would certainly deal with them again and again. Part of this lies with SCANs webfront, which is a well maintained and frequently updated. The other, and main reason is scans customer service is well informed and very capable. I was kept well informed of the state of my delivery, was guided through complicated tech, and helped to quickly overcome all issues arising from large component orders. in short, SCAN are easily one of the best retailers going and in terms of availability and service certainly beat high street retailers hands down. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 10/01/07 Nick_H Member Since: 10/01/07
View Member's: Reviews I ordered a couple of CD/DVD drives and was very impressed. E-mails were sent to me every step of the way from payment authorisation to despatch. I was able to change the delivery address after placing the order to one different from my credit card address -- no problem, and a reply from a real person! There was a possibility of a delayed despatch so I got an e-mail warning me of that too - although in the event there wasn't a problem. An the goods were shipped via a courier that offered package tracking via their website -- so I could check that the package had been delivered to its destination. I chose this merchant on price, but price isn't everything -- I've had really bad experiences elsewhere. But this time I have nothing but praise for Scan Computers. Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 06/01/07 johnalpha Member Since: 06/01/07
View Member's: Reviews A few months ago I bought a high-end gaming system from Scan Computers and I have nothing but praise for these people. For me at least, they really do deliver on what they promise. I used the Scan website 'configurator' to put together my 'dream system'. I had several useful chats with Scan's technical support guys before finalising the spec. They kept me informed throughout the build progress. The system was built with a high level of competence and care, with all the wiring neatly anchored and cabled away. I'm an experienced electronics engineer, and I couldn't have done a better job myself. I've also had a couple of chats with their technical support people and, like everybody at Scan that I've had contact with, they're consistently friendly and helpful in every way. (Maybe I need to say that I have no connection with Scan, other than as a (very) satisfied customer). Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 23/11/06 Barry666 Member Since: 23/11/06
View Member's: Reviews I first purchased a DVD drive from scan and had no problems. It was delivered on the day agreed. I then felt quite confident about placing a more substantial order. What a mistake that was. I ordered a CPU, Motherboard and Memory,which came to several hundred pounds, all items were in stock. I placed the order on a Monday night and was told they could be delivered on the Wednesday. As I could not arrange for someone to be there I changed it to Thursday. On Wednesday night at about 8.30 I received an email from scan telling me there was a delay for my order. What use is an email the night before your delivery when you have already made the arrangements to have someone there to receive it. I see scan has had good reviews and I would have given them the same if I had only had the one order. Try them a few times though and you might not have such a high opinion of them Overall Rating
Date Reviewed: 21/11/06 paultaylor25 Member Since: 21/11/06
View Member's: Reviews I don't understand the low reviews below. This is the best company I have ever dealt with. They could not do enough to help me and the end result (An Isotope iX system) is the best PC I have ever owned or used. In a time when customer service is seen as an add on SCAN are bucking the trend and basing their entire business model on it. I cannot reccomend them highly enough! Overall Rating
